			    STPJS 181</div>
  <p class="cont">of angels<span class="footRef">1</span> remained. All the prophets had the Melchizedek Priesthood and were ordained by God
  himself.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">2</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Elements Are Eternal</div>
  <p class="std">The elements are eternal.<span class="footRef">3</span> That which has a beginning will surely have an end; take a ring, it
  is without beginning or end<span class="footRef">4</span>&mdash;cut it for a beginning place and at the same time you have an ending
  place.</p>
  <p class="std">A key: Every principle proceeding from God is eternal<span class="footRef">5</span> and any principle which is not eternal
  is of the devil. The sun has no beginning or end; the rays which proceed from himself have no
  bounds, consequently are eternal.</p>
  <p class="std">So it is with God. If the soul of man<span class="footRef">6</span> had a beginning it will surely have an end. In the
  translation &ldquo;without form and void&rdquo;<span class="footRef">7</span> it should be read, empty and desolate. The word created<span class="footRef">8</span> should
  be formed, or organized.<span class="footRef">9</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Observation on the Sectarian God</div>
  <p class="std">&ldquo;That which is without body, parts and passions is nothing. There is no other God in heaven but
  that God who has flesh and bones.<span class="footRef">10</span> John 5:26. As the Father hath life in himself, even so hath he
  given to the Son to have life in himself.<span class="footRef">11</span> God the Father took life unto himself precisely as Jesus
  did.&rdquo;</p>
  <p class="std">&ldquo;The first step in salvation of man<span class="footRef">12</span> is the laws of eternal and self-existent principles. Spirits
  are eternal.<span class="footRef">13</span> At the first organization<span class="footRef">14</span> in heaven we were all present, and saw the Savior chosen and
  appointed<span class="footRef">15</span> and the plan of salvation made, and we sanctioned it.</p>
  <p class="std">&ldquo;We came to this earth that we might have a body and present it pure before God<span class="footRef">16</span> in the
  celestial kingdom. The great principle of happiness consists in having a body. The devil has no body,
  and herein is his punishment. He is pleased when he can obtain the tabernacle of man, and when cast
  out by the Savior he asked to go into the herd of swine,<span class="footRef">17</span> showing that he would prefer a swine&rsquo;s
  body to having none.</p>
  <p class="std">&ldquo;All beings who have bodies have power over those who have not. The devil has no power over
  us only as we permit him.<span class="footRef">18</span> The moment we revolt<span class="footRef">19</span> at anything which comes from God, the devil
  takes power. This earth will be rolled back into the presence of God,<span class="footRef">20</span> and crowned with celestial
  glory.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">21</span></p>
